d would also radicalize the innovations hardcore the two genres and their ideologies intertwined noticeably resulting two main genres one being metalcore The term has been used refer bands that were not purely hardcore nor purely metal such Earth Crisis Integrity and Hogans Heroes Metallica and Slayer pioneers the heavy metal subgenre thrash metal were influenced number hardcore bands Metallicas cover album Garage Inc included covers two Discharge and three Misfits songs while Slayers cover album Undisputed Attitude consisted covers predominately hardcore punk bands During the 2000s many more metalcore bands became known Bullet for Valentine Killswitch Engage Atreyu Shadows Fall and Lay Dying all had some popularity during the 2000s Some hardcore bands began experimenting with other styles their careers progressed the 1980s becoming known alternative rock Bands such Minutemen Meat Puppets Hsker and The Replacements drew from hardcore they had played earlier their careers but broke away from its loud and fast formula the mid1980s northern West Coast state bands such Melvins Flipper and Green River developed sludgy aggressive sound that melded the slower tempos heavy metal with the intensity hardcore creating alternative rock subgenre known grunge Grunge evolved from the local Seattle punk rock scene and was inspired bands such The Fartz Minute Warning and The Accsed Grunge fuses elements hardcore and heavy metal although some bands performed with more emphasis one the other Grunges key guitar influences included Black Flag and The Melvins Black Flags 1984 record War which the band combined heavy metal with their traditional sound made strong impact Seattle Digital hardcore music genre fusing elements hardcore punk and various forms electronic music and techno developed Germany during the early 1990s and often features sociological leftextremist lyrical themes Nintendocore another musical style fuses hardcore with video game music chiptunes and 8bit music The Washington state band Melvins aside from their influence grunge helped create what would known sludge metal which also combination between Black Sabbathstyle music and hardcore punk This genre developed during the early 1990s the Southern United States particularly the New Orleans metal scene Some the pioneering bands sludge metal were Eyehategod Crowbar Down Buzzoven Acid Bath and Corrosion Conformity Later bands such Isis and Neurosis with similar influences created style that relies mostly ambience and atmosphere that would eventually named atmospheric sludge metal postmetal 